# Add-on repository layout (kellerza/hass-addons)

This repo aggregates Home Assistant add-ons. Some folders are **maintained here**; others are
**CI-mirrored from upstream repos** by `.github/workflows/sync-remotes.yml` and will have any manual
edits **overwritten on the next sync**.

## Do NOT hand-edit — CI-synced mirrors

These folders are copied verbatim from another repo. Fix the problem in the **source repo**, not
here:

- **`hass-addon-sunsynk-edge/`**, **`hass-addon-sunsynk-multi/`**, **`hass-addon-mbusd/`** — synced
  from **`kellerza/sunsynk`**. Edit those add-ons in the `sunsynk` repo (per its own rules: edge is
  the dev add-on and Docker build source; multi is the stable/image-only release add-on).
  `Dockerfile` and `rootfs/` are stripped from both folders on sync (image-only mirrors).
- **`hass-addon-sma-em-edge/`** — synced from **`kellerza/hassio-sma-em`** (`sma-em-dev`; build
  source). The `slug` is rewritten by CI; don't fix it here. `Dockerfile` and `rootfs/` are stripped
  on sync (image-only mirror).

If a task would touch any of the above, **redirect**: state that the folder is a sync target and the
change belongs in the upstream repo (or in `sync-remotes.yml` if the sync logic itself is wrong).

## Maintained here

Manual work is welcome on the repo's own add-ons and their Python:

- **`hass-addon-control-group/`** + **`src/ha_addon_control_group/`**
- **`hass-addon-esp/`** + **`src/ha_addon_esp/`**
- **`hass-addon-qsusb64/`** + **`src/ha_addon_qsusb64/`**
- **`hass-addon-git-push/`** (shell/Docker only)
- **`src/ha_addon/`** — shared HA API helpers (`ha_api/`) used across add-ons.

Pattern: add-on **packaging** (`config.yaml`, `translations/`, `Dockerfile`, `rootfs/` s6 services)
lives in the `hass-addon-*` folder; **behaviour** lives in the matching `src/ha_addon_*` package.
Keep Supervisor options in sync between an add-on's `config.yaml`, its `translations/en.yaml`, and
the `options.py` of its `src` package.
